.TH "devm_drm_irq_install" 9 "devm_drm_irq_install" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_drm_irq_install \- install IRQ handler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_drm_irq_install
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int irq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "irq" 12
IRQ number to install the handler for
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
devm_drm_irq_install is a  help function of drm_irq_install.

if the driver uses devm_drm_irq_install, there is no need
to call drm_irq_uninstall when the drm module get unloaded,
as this will done automagically.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success or a negative error code on failure.
